            <h2>1. About Saniova</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova is a technology-focused digital platform dedicated to exploring the intersection of Artificial
                Intelligence (AI),
                Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), emerging technologies, startups, and future technology trends.
                Our website operates
                as a commercial media platform, providing in-depth insights, analysis, and curated content about the
                rapidly evolving tech
                landscape. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number (if voluntarily provided
                    through contact forms)</li>
                <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system, device identifiers, and
                    device specifications</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, clicks, scroll depth, articles
                    read, and interaction patterns</li>
                <li><strong>Cookies & Tracking:</strong> Session cookies, persistent cookies, pixel tags, and similar
                    tracking technologies</li>
                <li><strong>Feedback & Submissions:</strong> Comments, messages, inquiries, and user-generated content
                    submitted through our platform</li>
                <li><strong>Affiliate & Commercial Data:</strong> Referral sources, product clicks, purchase behavior,
                    and conversion tracking</li>
                <li><strong>Automated Collection:</strong> Data collected through web server logs, analytics platforms,
                    and advertising networks</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>As a commercial technology publication, we use collected information for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Content Delivery & Improvement:</strong> To deliver relevant AI and tech articles, customize
                    your experience, and improve content quality</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics & Research:</strong> To analyze user behavior, identify trends in AI and tech
                    interest, and measure content performance</li>
                <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to inquiries, provide customer support, and send
                    newsletters or updates about new technology insights</li>
                <li><strong>Monetization:</strong> To serve targeted advertisements, manage affiliate partnerships, and
                    generate revenue through sponsored content</li>
                <li><strong>Commercial Partnerships:</strong> To facilitate partnerships with tech companies, startups,
                    and AI-focused organizations</li>
                <li><strong>Compliance & Security:</strong> To enforce our Terms of Service, prevent fraud, and maintain
                    website security</li>
                <li><strong>Marketing & Promotion:</strong> To promote our content across platforms, conduct A/B
                    testing, and optimize marketing campaigns</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Cookies, Tracking & Advertising</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova uses cookies and tracking technologies to enhance user experience and support our commercial
                operations:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Necessary for website functionality, security, and user
                    authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Track user engagement with our AI and tech content to understand
                    reader interests</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising Cookies:</strong> Enable targeted advertising from Google, affiliate networks,
                    and tech companies relevant to our audience</li>
                <li><strong>Third-Party Tracking:</strong> Google Analytics, advertising networks, and affiliate
                    platforms may set cookies to track conversions and display behavior</li>
                <li><strong>Retargeting:</strong> We use retargeting pixels to show relevant tech and AI-related ads to
                    visitors across the web</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Users can control cookies through browser settings or opt-out of personalized advertising through
                Google's Ad Settings.
                However, disabling cookies may limit website functionality.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Third-Party Services & Integrations</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova partners with various technology and commercial platforms:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Google Analytics & Search Console:</strong> For traffic analysis and SEO monitoring</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising Networks:</strong> Google Ads, affiliate networks, and programmatic advertising
                    platforms</li>
                <li><strong>Cloudinary:</strong> For image hosting, optimization, and delivery</li>
                <li><strong>Email Services:</strong> For newsletter delivery and user communications</li>
                <li><strong>Affiliate Partners:</strong> Tech companies, AI platforms, and product review affiliates
                </li>
                <li><strong>Social Media Platforms:</strong> Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, Instagram for content
                    distribution</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                These third parties have their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for their data practices.
                We recommend reviewing their privacy policies separately.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Data Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
            <p>
                We may share your information with:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Advertising partners and networks for targeted ad delivery</li>
                <li>Affiliate companies for commission tracking and partnership management</li>
                <li>Analytics providers for understanding user behavior and content performance</li>
                <li>Law enforcement or government authorities when required by law</li>
                <li>Service providers who assist in website operations, hosting, and maintenance</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not sell personal information to unrelated third parties. However, we may share aggregated,
                anonymized data for research and commercial analytics purposes.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Data Security & Storage</h2>
            <p>
                We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data, including encryption,
                secure server protocols, and access controls. However, no transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
                We cannot guarantee absolute security of information transmitted through our platform. Your use of
                Saniova
                indicates acceptance of this security limitation.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Affiliate Disclosures & Monetization</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova is a commercial platform that generates revenue through:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Affiliate Marketing:</strong> Links to AI platforms, tech products, and tools may be
                    affiliate links. We earn commissions at no additional cost to you if you make a purchase</li>
                <li><strong>Sponsored Content:</strong> We may publish sponsored articles, reviews, and partnerships
                    with tech companies and startups</li>
                <li><strong>Display Advertising:</strong> Third-party ads relevant to AI, technology, and business
                    interests appear throughout the site</li>
                <li><strong>Premium Content:</strong> Future premium features or exclusive content may require payment
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                All sponsored content and affiliate relationships are disclosed. We maintain editorial integrity while
                supporting our business model.
            </p>

            <h2>9. Your Rights & Choices</h2>
            <p>
                Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your data:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of personal information we hold about you</li>
                <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Update or correct inaccurate information</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request removal of your personal data (subject to legal requirements)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from newsletters and marketing communications</li>
                <li><strong>Cookie Control:</strong> Manage or disable cookies through browser settings</li>
                <li><strong>Targeted Ads:</strong> Opt-out of personalized advertising through Google and other networks
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                To exercise these rights, contact us at the information provided in the Contact Us section.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Children & COPPA Compliance</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova is not directed toward children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
                personal information from children. If we become aware that we have collected data from a child under
                13,
                we will promptly delete it. Parents or guardians concerned about data collection can contact us
                directly.
            </p>

            <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova operates from multiple locations. Your information may be transferred to,
                stored in, and processed in countries other than your residence, which may have different
                data protection laws. By using Saniova, you consent to such transfers.
            </p>

            <h2>12. Retention of Data</h2>
            <p>
                We retain personal information as long as necessary to provide services and fulfill legal obligations.
                Analytics data is typically retained for up to 24 months. You can request deletion of your personal data
                at any time,
                subject to legal and business requirements.
            </p>

            <h2>13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time to reflect changes in our practices,
                technology, legal requirements, or other factors. Significant changes will be announced on our website
                with a revised date. Your continued use of Saniova following any modifications indicates acceptance of
                the updated policy.
            </p>

            <h2>14. GDPR, CCPA & Data Protection Laws</h2>
            <p>
                Saniova respects global data protection regulations including GDPR (EU), CCPA (California),
                and similar laws. Users from these regions have additional rights regarding their data.
                For specific requests or inquiries related to these regulations, please contact us directly.
            </p>

            <h2>15. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                For questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, data access,
                or to exercise your rights, please contact us through our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
                We aim to respond to inquiries within 30 days.
            </p>
